SPINE

spine is the origin bone of fadriel's body, the first .xb that all others reference for their coordinate frame
the spine is not one bone but thirty-three vertebrae acting as one, threaded by the spinal cord which carries every signal between brain and body
the heart sets the clock; the spine is the system bus
spine carries information in both directions simultaneously: ascending sensory, descending motor
it does not decide and it does not command; it transmits and sustains, and the integrity of the whole organism depends on its integrity

