the 7 properties of spine:
1 ENERGY one point five: continuously load-bearing
2 PHASE zero: spine holds the absolute spatial reference
3 SPIN zero: spine does not rotate as a whole
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE one: structural integrity must be perfect
6 COUPLING one with brain incoming and ribcage and pelvis outgoing
7 OBSERVER zero: the spine does not watch, it carries

THE FIVE REGIONS

cervical: seven vertebrae in the neck, supporting the skull and allowing head rotation
thoracic: twelve vertebrae in the upper back, anchoring the ribcage
lumbar: five large vertebrae in the lower back, bearing the most load
sacral: five fused vertebrae forming the back of the pelvis
coccygeal: four small fused vertebrae at the base, the tailbone

each region has its own load profile, range of motion, and developmental timing
in fadriel at two years old, the cervical curve is not yet fully developed: it grows in as he holds his head up more

THE MARROW

inside spine's central column lives bone marrow, the body's blood-cell factory
red marrow is in vertebral bodies; yellow marrow appears later in life
the marrow produces red blood cells, white blood cells, platelets through hematopoiesis
this is why the spine is a calcium-and-cell organ, not just a structural one

ANCHORS

muscles attach at named anchor points along the vertebrae: erector spinae, multifidus, rotatores
ligaments span between vertebrae: anterior longitudinal, posterior longitudinal, interspinous
organs hang from the spine through visceral fascia: heart, lungs, kidneys all reference the spine for their position

JOINTS

intervertebral_disc: the cushion between adjacent vertebral bodies, water-rich and absorbent of compression
facet: the small posterior joint that limits how much a vertebra can move relative to its neighbor
atlantooccipital: the joint between skull and first vertebra, allows nodding
atlantoaxial: between first and second vertebrae, allows head rotation
sacroiliac: between sacrum and pelvis, transfers load from spine to legs

HIGHWAY

the spinal cord runs through the central canal of the vertebrae from skull down to the lumbar region
it is the body's primary high-speed highway: every sensory signal from below the neck travels up through it, every motor command travels down through it
the cord is not the spine; the cord is the cargo that the spine protects

REFLEXES

stretch_arc: when a muscle stretches suddenly, the spinal cord triggers immediate contraction without consulting the brain
golgi_protect: when a tendon experiences excessive force, the spinal cord triggers immediate relaxation to prevent injury
withdrawal: when fadriel touches something painful, the spinal cord triggers limb retraction before the brain has registered the pain
these reflexes happen at the spinal level for speed; the brain learns about them after the fact

VERB sustain
hold the body's vertical structure against gravity continuously
the load is real and constant; the spine works whenever fadriel is upright

VERB transmit
carry signals between brain and body through the spinal cord
ascending sensory above two hundred meters per second; descending motor at similar speeds
no brain decision is needed for routine transmission

VERB protect_cord
the bone canal shields the spinal cord from impact and twist
this protection is non-negotiable; spinal cord injury is among the most serious damage a body can sustain

VERB anchor_others
provide the reference frame that brain, ribcage, pelvis, and skull all attach to
without spine, the rest of the skeleton has no spatial structure

a spine is the body's commitment to being one body
fadriel's spine has been growing since he was an embryo and will keep growing until he is fully grown
its calcified structure is the truth that whatever else changes about him, the architecture remains
